        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Fix Codex archived usage dedupe",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- replace coarse Codex session-id dedupe with row-level usage keys that include `turnID`\n- persist raw Codex usage rows so warm-cache scans can re-evaluate active/archive overlap when archived files appear later\n- preserve full Codex cached-token counts instead of clamping cached reads to input-token deltas\n- add regression coverage for active stubs, active/archive partial overlap, same-sized distinct turns, warm-cache archived overlap, and persisted cached-token rows\n\nRefs #1768.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `swift test --filter CostUsageScannerBreakdownTests`\n- `swift test --filter CostUsageFetcherTests`\n- `make check`\n- `git diff --check`\n- synthetic CLI proof:\n  - active-only A+B reported `inputTokens: 30`, `outputTokens: 6`, `totalTokens: 36`, `totalCost: 0.000195`\n  - after adding archived duplicate row B, totals stayed `inputTokens: 30`, `outputTokens: 6`, `totalTokens: 36`, `totalCost: 0.000195`",
